​Introduction
In this Privacy Policy, “Mad Hook” refers to Mad Hook LLC, a developer and publisher of games and mobile game applications based in Jordan. Mad Hook is a game development studio that develops and publishes games on multiple platforms including mobile phones.
Mad Hook is committed to protecting the privacy of its users and providing them with a better gaming experience.
We respect your privacy and have devoted our efforts to ensure all Personal Information and details are secured as possible, subject to the T&Cs and the Privacy Policy that is incorporated into the T&Cs. The defined terms under this Privacy Policy refer to the interpretation and terms under the T&Cs unless otherwise provided in this Privacy Policy or otherwise defined herein.
Please take the time to read carefully the Privacy Policy as by using any of our Platform(s), web page(s), websites and applications owned by or operated by Mad Hook “Platform” you automatically agree that you have read and accepted to be bound by our T&Cs and Privacy Policy. The type of information we collect may vary depending on your use of our Platform and Services;
By using the Platform and Services, You understand and do not object to the collection, disclosure, storage and use of Your Personal Information as outlined in this Privacy Policy. If You do not want Mad Hook to collect, store, use or share Your Personal Information in the ways described in this Privacy Policy, You should not play games developed by Mad Hook or use Our Platform or any of Our Services.
When we say “Mad Hook”, “application”, “our,” “we,” or “us,” we’re talking about Mad Hook LLC and any of its subsidiaries, all Mad Hook applications and Services available at our website. This Privacy Policy (“Privacy Policy”) applies to all of our websites, applications, services, features, software, products, content, Madhook.io and/or the other domains provided by Mad Hook (together, “Services”) unless specified otherwise.
The purpose of this policy is to provide you with all the important information and explanations about how and why some of your data may be collected and processed by Mad Hook when you use one of our applications or browse on our website or use any of our Services. This privacy policy governs and details the main principles that Mad Hook applies to the data we collect and process, to:
(i) develop and publish mobile apps (“Mad Hook Apps and Games”),
(ii) serve advertising that are tailored to the interests of users (“Mad Hook Ads”) and
(iii) run our corporate website (“www.madhook.io”).
This Privacy Policy also aims to remind you about your rights and to provide you with all the elements you need to exercise them.
Should you have any questions related to this Privacy Policy or our practices around privacy and data protection in general, please don’t hesitate to contact Mad Hook support email as indicated in the contact section of this Privacy Policy.
Mad Hook Apps and Games
Why does Mad Hook collect data from its apps and games?
When you install and use Mad Hook mobile applications, we can collect and process some of your data for different legitimate purposes.
You will find below explanations regarding the reasons why Mad Hook may collect data and the legal bases Mad Hook relies on in each case.
Mad Hook collects data:
To provide you with the services you asked for (e.g., Knowing how many users completed the first 10 levels)
Legal basis – such data processing is strictly necessary for the service(s) asked
To run analytics and understand how users interact with our product, applications and Services in order to continuously improve it
(e.g., Knowing that some obstacles are hard to overcome based on user progression)
Legal basis - Express consent. Mad Hook only processes or shares personal data collected through Mad Hook apps for analytics purposes once you express your consent through the pop-up notice included in our apps.
To serve advertising tailored to the preference and interests of our users
and allow Mad Hook to continue to provide free services and products
Legal basis – Express consent. Mad Hook only processes or shares personal data collected through Mad Hook apps for personalized advertising purposes once you express your consent through the pop-up notice included in one of our apps.
For all data processing activities that rely on users’ consent, you can withdraw your consent at any time from the “settings” page in our various applications.
Please only note that in the case where you withdraw your consent or where you refuse to consent in the first place, you will still be served with advertising but that may be less relevant to you as it will not be tailored to your interests.
The legal basis for collecting and using the Personal Information and data depends on what the Personal Information and data is and the context in which We collect the data.
In accordance with Article 6 of the General Data Protection Regulation “GDPR”, We will process Your Personal Information for the purposes of Mad Hook’s legitimate interests pursued for ensuring secure optimization and improvement of Our Services, Platform and performance and for efficiently fulfilling Our contractual obligations. In some cases, the processing is necessary for the compliance and fulfillment of a legal obligation, or to protect Your vital interests or those of another natural person/user.
What data does Mad Hook collect from its apps and games?
“Personal Information” in this Privacy Policy is individual information about personal or objective circumstances of a specific or identifiable person, e.g. Your name, address or e-mail address, IP addresses and device-related identifiers.
For the purposes of providing you with the Services listed above and on our Platforms, and to the extent necessary to fulfil one or more of its functions and activities, by reasonable means, you provide us with your Personal Information and details with your consent to use, share and make available, where applicable, to other users and/or any Third-Party or the public as deemed necessary.
Usage Information
Whenever you use or visit our Platform and Services, Mad Hook, uses a variety of technologies to collect information about you (“Usage Information”). Usage Information include without limitations, the name of your internet service provider, the browser and the type of machine (“Device Type”), operating system, application, the time, the page served and the preceding page views and your use of features on the application version you are using, and any website that may refer you to us and the pages you visit to help manage and enhance the application. In addition to technical information about the device you use and your connection (user agent, type of connection, timestamp).
Device Identifier
Whenever you use or visit our application and services, Mad Hook, uses a variety of technologies to collect information about you your IP address or other unique identifiers for any device you use to access and use our application such as (computer, mobile phone, tablet or any other device). We, our affiliates, service providers, business partners or any third party may use a device identifier among other things, to administer the application; help diagnose problems, analyze trends, track users’ web page movement over time and access different websites, platforms or other mobile, online or offline services. We collect and identify your device primarily using your mobile device advertising identifier, e.g. Apple’s iOS Identifier for Advertising (IDFA) or Google’s Android Advertising ID, as well as other identifiers, which are technical identifiers developed by mobile operating systems for advertising purposes which remain under your control and can be reset or erased at any time in through your device settings.
Personal Information
We may collect Personal Information (information that can be used to identify you as an individual) such as, name, email, telephone number, home address, demographic information (zip code, age), contact details (phone book) and/or payment information such as account or credit card numbers and details). In addition to Data pertaining to your activities on our applications, website and Services and notably the way in which you interact with our applications, website and Services (for how long do you use our application everyday) and with the advertising served in our applications (how many ads you see per day).
Information from Others.
We collect information about you when we receive it from other users, third parties, and affiliates. For example, when you connect your account to third-party services or sign in using a third-party partner (like Google Play Game Services, iOS Game Center or Facebook), we collect information in accordance with the privacy policies and authorization procedures determined by those services. The information We receive depends on which Mad Hook game You’re playing, others or third-parties application, and Your privacy settings.
Other Information You Provide to Us.
When You provide us with additional information other than the information under this Privacy Policy, We collect the information, for example when You provide Us you’re your financial data, or when you communicate with others or post, use messenger or chat services, upload or store content, contact our Support team, or provide billing information, You give Us Your consent to process the provided information for the intended purpose
How We Use the Information We Collect
We use information we have collected and stored for a variety of reasons; to provide you with Our Services, a better gaming experience and/or information you request, such as new games information alerts, promotions, participate in promotional activities, or otherwise, including without limitation:
Create Your game accounts;
Improve our Services, Platform, applications and Your experience;
Respond to your questions, inquiries and requests, such as, games information, alerts and provide customer support services and technical support;
Advice you of important safety-related information;
Enable you to participate in activities or programs and communicate with other users;
Notify You of game and application updates, new content and/or offers;
Verify your identity, and prevent fraud or illegal activities;
Provide you with access to the website, applications and some areas and features such as your interactions with other users;
Communicate with you about your account and activities on the applications and in our sole discretion change to any Mad Hook policy or notice;
Tailor, manage and deliver content, advertisements;
For our records to enable us to operate and provide our Services, including providing users support, and improving, fixing, and customizing our Services, website and applications by developing and testing new services and features.
Comply with the license and legal obligations, where applicable.
With whom may your data be shared & why?
Mad Hook does not share your personal data with third parties without your prior consent. When you consent to the collection of data for advertising and analytics purpose, we may share the data listed above with the following categories of recipients:
With Your Consent. We will share information with companies, organizations, or individuals outside of Mad Hook only when we have your consent to do so.
With Service Providers. We provide Personal Information to trusted partners who work on our behalf based on our instructions and in compliance with appropriate confidentiality measures.
For Legal and Other Purposes. We may access, preserve, and disclose information to investigate, prevent, or take action in connection with: (i) legal process and legal requests; (ii) enforcement of our Terms of Service; (iii) claims that any content violates the rights of third parties; (iv) protecting the rights, property or personal safety of Mad Hook, its users, or the public; (v) establishing or exercising our legal rights or defending against legal claims; or (vi) as otherwise required by law.
With Ad Partners: We may allow others to provide analytics services and serve advertisements on our behalf across the internet and in applications. These entities may use cookies, device identifiers, and other technologies to collect information about your use of the Services, websites and applications, including your IP address, web browser, mobile network information, pages viewed, time spent on pages, or in apps, links clicked and conversion information. Which allows us to monetize the ad inventory of our apps and provide users with free products and services.
