Advertisements
Why does Mad Hook collect data for advertising purposes?
Mad Hook monetizes advertising inventory by allowing advertisers to serve personalized advertising to users.
In order to deliver such services for its clients and partners, Mad Hook can receive and process data for different legitimate purposes.
You will find below explanations regarding the reasons why Mad Hook may collect data and the legal bases it relies on in each case.
To personalize the Services and provide advertisements, content, or features that are targeted toward your interests (behavioral advertising).
To help our publisher partners monetize their ad inventory
Just like Mad Hook relies on advertising to provide free apps and games, our partners can use Mad Hook Ads services to monetize their ad inventory.
To help advertiser partners promote their products and services
Mad Hook helps advertisers promote their products and services to an audience that has demonstrated interests in similar products and services and allows them to optimize their marketing spends.
● To create analytics and reports for external parties, including partners, publishers, advertisers, apps, third-parties and the public regarding the use of and trends within our Services and ads, including showing trends to partners regarding general preferences, the effectiveness of ads, and information on user experiences.
What data does Mad Hook collect for advertising purposes?
For the purposes of providing you with the Services listed above on our applications, you provide us with your Personal Information and details with your consent to use, share and make available, where applicable, to other users and/or any Third-Party or the public. The data we collect is limited to the aforementioned points under “Mad Hook Apps and Games” of this Privacy Policy in addition to Data pertaining to your interactions with the advertisements served (e.g., number of ads served, potential clicks), Your game social network ID and any contextual data about Your game play such as Your level and other technical information.
With whom is your data shared & why?
Data collected for the purposes of Ad serving are only shared with the following category of recipients and only to the extent such data is necessary for the purpose they are following, which are advertisers that advertise inside our applications and Platforms to serve personalized or non-personalized advertising. When clicking on a third-party advertisement, You will no longer be on a Service or Platform provided by Mad Hook.
Mad Hook Website
Why does Mad Hook collect data from its website?
Like on most websites, when you browse on Mad Hook.io certain information about your connection and device(s) are automatically collected for the website to operate properly.
Mad Hook and its partners also use cookies and similar technologies to analyze how our users interact with our services and administer the website. Cookies are small text files stored on your browser that allow the collection of non-personally identifiable information related to your navigation on a website.
You can control the use of cookies in your browser settings but if you choose to disable cookies it may affect certain websites’ functionalities.
What data does Mad Hook collect from its website?
For the purposes listed above the data that Mad Hook and its partners collect is limited to:
Browsing events and interactions with the website’s contents and services
Cookie identifiers, IP address and technical information related to your browser and/or device (user agent)
Information you provide us with voluntarily when you contact Mad Hook
Analytics and Third-Party Cookies
Mad Hook uses Weebly to collect information related to the web traffic on our website. This service allows us to measure the performance and proper functioning of our website and to provide you with a better experience. For more information on the data protection and privacy aspects of these analytics services, you can refer to Weebly privacy policy accessible here:
https://www.weebly.com/privacy
​Mad Hook uses technologies such as Device Identifiers and Cookies (data files placed on a device when its used to visit the application) to collect information and help analyze page view and flow, in addition, to associate users with social networking sites. Please be aware that some features and functionalities may not work properly without using Cookies because we may not be able to recognize and associate you with your Mad Hook account. As such, if you block or delete cookies, not all tracking that we have described in our Privacy Policy will stop. Also, please note that Third-Parties may opt to use cookies or similar files on your device to personalize your experience on their websites or applications. You may opt to decline cookies at any time.
Social Networks and other Communication Tools
Our website also offers communication tools allowing users to share content on social networks. When you interact with such social media widgets or “share buttons”, these social network companies may collect information about you and/or your device and connection. Your interactions with these services are governed by the respective privacy policies of the companies providing these services. For more information on the data protection and privacy practices of these companies, you can refer to their specific policies listed below:
